JOHANNESBURG - Free State police have arrested two suspects in connection with the murder of seven farm workers in Kestell. The bodies of six women and a young man were discovered inside a house at Lismore farm on Friday. It's understood that the victims -  a 17-year-old boy and six women between the ages of 22 and 53 years old were shot several times. The owner of the farm discovered the bodies and alerted authorities. Free State police spokesperson Sam Makhele said intelligence-driven information led to the arrest of the two suspects. Two firearms, a shotgun, and a pellet gun were recovered. Police are looking into the possibility that one of the weapons was used during the murders.